        "cooked": "<blockquote>\n<p>2002 Piper-Heidsieck Champagne Cuv\u00e9e Rare - France, Champagne (11/11/2020)<br>\nAnother big house champagne that showed good quality and consistency. 70% chard, higher dosage than the Billecart-Salmon, more exotic and tropical fruits that were slightly coarser on the palate, but still had the rich and brioche notes that typify grandes marques.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Really nice bottle.  I remember these were on WTSO for around $120 and bottle is cool looking.   <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/c/c91f538423a6b19a38f6c5ca9219bf69f143e0bb.gif\" width=\"100\" height=\"70\" alt=\"champagne.gif\" title=\"champagne.gif\" class=\"animated\"></p>",
