        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/ecb155/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2020-11-12T06:41:31.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"165564\">\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>2002 Piper-Heidsieck Champagne Cuv\u00e9e Rare - France, Champagne (11/11/2020)<br>\nAnother big house champagne that showed good quality and consistency. 70% chard, higher dosage than the Billecart-Salmon, more exotic and tropical fruits that were slightly coarser on the palate, but still had the rich and brioche notes that typify grandes marques.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Really nice bottle.  I remember these were on WTSO for around $120 and bottle is cool looking.   <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/c/c91f538423a6b19a38f6c5ca9219bf69f143e0bb.gif\" width=\"100\" height=\"70\" alt=\"champagne.gif\" title=\"champagne.gif\" class=\"animated\"></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Hi John, yes definitely bling bling with a ring on it - despite its appearance it\u2019s a very serious champagne!</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"165564\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"165564\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>One of the pioneers in organic farming in champagne in the 90s when production of champagne was much more industrial than artisanal.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>From the simple perspective of production volume, the past tense is not warranted! In terms of \u201cdiscursive presence\u201d perhaps it is\u2026</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Hi William, was thinking of in terms of production quality but for volume definitely you are right!</p>",
